bug.short_desc: [source lookup][debug view] After terminating a suspended process, the IP remains in editor.

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86220 Screen shot with the left-over IP in editor.
The source lookup does not clean up the IP annotations in editors when the process is terminated.
*** Bug 218876 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
See comments in bug 218876 about possible solutions.
With change in IRunControl.IExitedDMEvent (bug 224434), it should now be possible to fix this bug without introducing unwanted dependencies.
On second thought, this will probably take more work than I can hope to handle before M6.
At also accumulates with several runs. At least it should cleaning existing ip marker before adding new

Created attachment 98516 Patch with fix.
The patch adds two new events: MIInferiorProcess.InferiorStartedDMEvent MIInferiorProcess.InferiorExitedDMEvent which implement the IRunControl execution context started/exited events. Based on these events the source locator service can erase the IP annotations when the process exits.
I committed the fix. Marc please verify.
